net.nemerosa.ontrack.ui.resource

Class Resource<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.nemerosa.ontrack.ui.resource.LinkContainer<Resource<T>>
      • net.nemerosa.ontrack.ui.resource.Resource<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of data to wrap into the resource
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ViewSupplier

    public class Resource<T>
extends LinkContainer<Resource<T>>
implements ViewSupplier
    The resource wrapper class might be used for UI return types whenever:
    • a model object is not applicable, when describing an API for example
    • the links cannot be derived from the model object because the resource maybe served by different controllers
